  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: `geth version`  : 1.4.17\nOS & Version: Windows/Linux/OSX  : Linux\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)  : 5a6008e\n#### Actual behaviour\n\n`Out Of Memory` Occurred frequently when i run the `geth`.  Here is some error log\n\n```\n I1012 02:56:05.031681 core/blockchain.go:975] imported 2048 block(s) (0 queued 0 ignored) including 15673 txs in 56.217819928s. #1717531 [6ce8e172 / 87efe14f]\nfatal error: runtime: out of memory\n\nruntime stack:\nruntime.throw(0xd15ce3, 0x16)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/panic.go:566 +0x95\nruntime.sysMap(0xc468c70000, 0x2000000, 0x0, 0x1540d38)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/mem_linux.go:219 +0x1d0\nruntime.(*mheap).sysAlloc(0x1527680, 0x2000000, 0x1)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/malloc.go:407 +0x37a\nruntime.(*mheap).grow(0x1527680, 0x1000, 0x0)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/mheap.go:726 +0x62\nruntime.(*mheap).allocSpanLocked(0x1527680, 0x1000, 0x7f4fd67ea068)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/mheap.go:630 +0x4f2\nruntime.(*mheap).alloc_m(0x1527680, 0x1000, 0x7f0100000000, 0x435c4e)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/mheap.go:515 +0xe0\nruntime.(*mheap).alloc.func1()\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/mheap.go:579 +0x4b\nruntime.systemstack(0x7f4fecac5dd8)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/asm_amd64.s:314 +0xab\nruntime.(*mheap).alloc(0x1527680, 0x1000, 0x10100000000, 0x7f4fecac5e58)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/mheap.go:580 +0x73\nruntime.largeAlloc(0x2000000, 0x7f4fecac5e01, 0x46893a)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/malloc.go:774 +0x93\nruntime.mallocgc.func1()\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/malloc.go:669 +0x3e\nruntime.systemstack(0xc42001ea00)\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/asm_amd64.s:298 +0x79\nruntime.mstart()\n    /usr/lib/go-1.7/src/runtime/proc.go:1079\n```\n\nShould I configure the linux machine memory limit ? \n\nHere is my system configure\n\n```\ncore file size          (blocks, -c) 0\ndata seg size           (kbytes, -d) unlimited\nscheduling priority       